        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 30 at 5:22AM CDT until April 30 at 5:45AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 521 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Anson, moving
east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe storm will be near...
Anson and Hawley around 525 AM CDT.
Nugent, Avoca, and Lueders around 535 AM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include Funston,
Hodges, Big Country Baptist Assembly, Truby, and The Intersection Of
Us-180 And Farm Road 600.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
